gomodel:SYNGO_2800  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.4: \"Fz1 overexpression induces presynaptic protein clustering\"\n- \"At 9 DIV, hippocampal neurons transfected with Fz1-myc showed increased numbers of Bassoon puncta compared to control neurons transfected with the empty vector (pCS2+; Figure Figure4F),4F), strongly supporting a role for Fz1 in presynaptic differentiation.\"\n\nFig.5: \"Wnt-3a induces presynaptic differentiation in cultured hippocampal neurons mediated by the Fz1 receptor.\"\n\n[Fig.6: \"Wnt-3a stimulates synaptic vesicle release in mature cultured hippocampal neurons\"]. Experimental description: - \"Rat hippocampal cultures were prepared as described previously [42,43].\"\n- Species of Fz1 is mouse (traced back via supplier R&D systems)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2800" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

